How to Deploy React website on Git using git pages.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mdO18zv3oGQ
How To Host React JS Website Live for Free using GitHub in 2020
Thapa Technical 
==========================================================

step 1:

Step 1A:
First we have to work in our local system
git bash open karavu

git status
git init
git staus
git add .
git commit -m '<my Message>'
Step 1B
git remote add origin https://github.com/aniruddhkadia/React18Ecommerce-app.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main


Step 1B:
We have to login in git-browser
create repository
kai pan select karavanu nai (README Select nai karavanu)

==========================================================

step 2 
We have to createt git page
Ref: https://create-react-app.dev/docs/deployment/


1. Add following in package.json file
"homepage": "https://aniruddhkadia.github.io/React18Ecommerce-app",

2. RUN follwoing command in vs code where is react app.
npm install --save gh-pages

3. Add following in package.json file under scripts
"predeploy": "npm run build",
"deploy": "gh-pages -d build",
 
4. RUN follwoing command in vs code where is react app.
npm run deploy

Site is now ready in git browser.
https://aniruddhkadia.github.io/React18Ecommerce-app/

 
 




